<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-445-310  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 445 310.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  July 10 1989 n323 p79(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>OS_: what's available? (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Neupert, Peter.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>OS-2 favors the C programming language over others because OS-2itself is written in C, making the interface easy.andP;  But,applications written in other languages such as FORTRAN or COBOLcan be easily converted to run with OS-2.andP;  Many mainframe FORTRANand COBOL applications are in the process of being converted toOS-2, and in many cases making changes is unnecessary.andP;  More than65 companies have developed languages and tools for OS-2, withproducts ranging from traditional languages to newer languagessuch as Modula-2 and Ada, as well as fourth-generation languagessuch as Information Builders' PC_ocus.andP;  Six OEMs offerPresentation Manager with OS-2, including IBM, NCR Corp, CompaqComputer Corp, Zenith Data Systems Corp, Bull and Nokia.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   OS/2 Presentation Manager (Graphical user interface) (usage).andO;Topic:     OS-2Programming LanguagesSoftware PackagesC Programming Language.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>